text: Chenar Shahijan County () is a county in Fars Province, Iran. At the 2016 census, its population was 45,638, in 9,187 families. The county has one city: Qaemiyeh. The county has two rural districts (dehestan): Anarestan Rural District and Somghan Rural District. The Chenar Shahijan County was established on 2018 in Fars province. == References == Category:Counties in Fars Province
title: Chenar Shahijan County
